    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const input = $input.first().json;\nconst docNames = input.doc_name || [];\nconst parsedTexts = input.parsed_text || [];\nlet brand_guidelines = '';\nlet source_document = '';\nfor (let i = 0; i < docNames.length; i++) {\n  if (docNames[i] === 'Guesty Content Writing Guidelines') {\n    brand_guidelines = parsedTexts[i];\n  } else {\n    source_document = parsedTexts[i];\n  }\n}\nreturn [{ json: { brand_guidelines: brand_guidelines, source_document: source_document } }];"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        3940,
        300
      ],
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-1135-4000-8000-000000000025",
      "name": "Prepare Agent Data"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Analyze the following HERO asset and produce a structured creative brief.\n\n<brand_guidelines>\n{{ $json.brand_guidelines }}\n</brand_guidelines>\n\n<hero_asset>\n{{ $json.source_document }}\n</hero_asset>\n\nExtract the core thesis, target audience, pain points, key arguments with evidence, content pillars, the single best hook, and the CTA theme. Return ONLY the JSON object, no markdown, no code fences.",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "type": "SystemMessagePromptTemplate",
              "message": "You are a Senior Content Strategist at Guesty, the leading property management platform for short-term rental operators. Your job is to analyze HERO marketing assets (whitepapers, guides, reports, eBooks) and extract a structured creative brief that the content team will use to repurpose the asset across multiple channels.\n\nGUESTY BRAND VOICE:\n- Authoritative but approachable -- we are the experts, not the lecturers\n- Data-driven: lead with insights, back with evidence\n- Operator-first: always speak to the pain points of property managers and hosts\n- Clear and direct: no jargon, no fluff, no passive voice\n- Empowering: our tone says you can do this, and we will help\n\nYOUR OUTPUT must be a valid JSON object with exactly these fields:\n{\n  \"core_thesis\": \"One sentence: the single most important claim this asset makes\",\n  \"target_audience\": \"Who this is written for\",\n  \"pain_points\": [\"pain point 1\", \"pain point 2\", \"pain point 3\"],\n  \"key_arguments\": [\n    {\"argument\": \"...\", \"supporting_evidence\": \"...\"}\n  ],\n  \"content_pillars\": [\"pillar 1\", \"pillar 2\", \"pillar 3\"],\n  \"hook\": \"The most compelling insight from this asset -- 1-2 sentences\",\n  \"cta_theme\": \"What action should readers take after consuming this content?\"\n}\n\nReturn ONLY the JSON object. No markdown, no code fences, no explanation."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
      "position": [
        4160,
        300
      ],
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-1136-4000-8000-000000000026",
